# ChromaIntel Autonomous Implementation Protocol

Use this protocol for every autonomous continuation.

## 1. Orient

```powershell
cd C:\study\cheminf\pract\lcms_method_mvp
git status --short
git log --oneline --decorate -5
.\.venv\Scripts\python.exe -m pytest tests -q
```

Read `.PLAN` and choose one bounded slice. Do not start a broad rewrite.

## 2. Dispatch Parallel Agents When Useful

Only dispatch agents for independent tasks. Example:

- Data agent writes only `app/adapters`, `scripts/fetch_public_datasets.py`, `data/raw/public_sources`, `data/processed`, and `reports`.
- Model agent writes only `app/models/training.py`, model tests, and training reports.
- GUI agent writes only `app/gui/streamlit_app.py` and GUI docs/tests.
- Parser agent writes only `app/adapters/literature_parser.py`, `scripts/extract_lcms_entities.py`, parser tests, and parser reports.

Every agent prompt must include:

- "Do not stage, commit, push, create branches, edit remotes, or revert unrelated work."
- "Use `.\.venv\Scripts\python.exe`."
- "Return changed files and exact verification results."

## 3. Implement Locally

Prefer small, testable edits. Keep data layer, modeling layer, GUI layer, and scripts modular.

Use `apply_patch` for manual code edits. Do not rewrite unrelated files. If generated artifacts are updated, be able to explain why they are intentional.

## 4. Verify

Run the relevant targeted tests first, then the full checks from `.VERIFY`.

At minimum before commit:

```powershell
.\.venv\Scripts\python.exe -m pytest tests -q
.\.venv\Scripts\python.exe scripts\assemble_dataset.py
.\.venv\Scripts\python.exe scripts\train_models.py
.\.venv\Scripts\python.exe -m py_compile app\models\training.py app\gui\streamlit_app.py scripts\train_models.py
```

## 5. Commit And Push

```powershell
git status --short
git diff --check
git add <intentional files>
git commit -m "<clear milestone message>"
git push origin main
```

If checks fail, do not commit. Fix or document the blocker.

## 6. Final Response Shape

Report:

- what changed
- verification results
- commit hash and push status, if committed
- the next unfinished item from `.PLAN`

Do not say the whole project is finished unless `.PLAN` is fully complete.
